author: Gary Pinneo
title: High School Sports Round-up: Boy's Soccer, Girl's Soccer, Golf, Volleyball, Corss Country
text: Posted Oct. 2, 2015 at 1:08 PM By Gary Pinneo Posted Oct. 2, 2015 at 1:08 PM Boyâ€™s Soccer Wayne 2 Penn Yan 0 The Mustang boy's soccer team was shutout by Wayne 2-0 in a Finger Lakes East contest on MondaySept. 28 in Penn Yan. The Wayne Eagles (8-0) remain undefeated in the FL East with the win. Jon McKay recorded 10 saves for Penn Yan in goal. Penn Yan 3 Pal-Mac 0 On Wednesday evening in Penn Yan, the Mustangs rebounded nicely to shutout Pal-Mac 3-0 in another Finger Lakes East match. Penn Yan's talented scorer Tate Stewart notched two first half goals to lead the Orange and Blue. Robbie Wigsten scored Penn Yan's other goal. Noah Hullings and Scot Fingar posted assists. Jon McKay had 6 saves in goal for Penn Yan (6-4-2, 5-2-2). Naples 5 Marcus Whitman 0 The Big Green of Naples shutout Marcus Whitman 5-0 in Naples on Sept. 28. Zach Payne and Tim Cornish combined for 13 saves in the nets for Whitman. The Wildcat's Finger Lakes West record falls to 1-6 with the loss. they are 2-8 overall. Dundee/Bradford 6 Hammondsport 0 The Dundee/Bradford combined boy's soccer team shutout Hammondsport 6-0 in Hammondsport on Thursday afternoon. The Scots offense was led by Austin Spina. He scored 4 goals for Dundee. Yannick Wohlhauser and Issek Pierce added the other 2 Dundee tallies. Geordyn Conyers and Jacob Rosnola added assists. The Dundee/Bradford netminder recorded nine saves to pick up the shutout win. Girl's Soccer Newark 2 Penn Yan 0 The Penn Yan Mustang girl's soccer team entertained Newark Sept. 29 at Mustang Field in a Finger Lakes East match. The visiting Reds scored a goal in each half and held the hometown Mustangs off the scoreboard en route to a 2-0 win. Kailee Christiansen had 9 saves for Penn Yan in goal. Waterloo 2 Marcus Whitman 1 The Waterloo Indian girl's soccer team scored 2 unanswered goals in the second half to erase a 1-0 Whitman lead and held to defeat the Wildcats 2-1 in Gorham Sept. 29. Whitman jumped out to an early 1-0 lead on a goal by Emily Thompson, but could not make this single tally stand up. Makayla Prusinowski picked up an assist on the Thompson goal. Katrina Meyer recorded 5 saves in goal for Whitman. Naples 2 Marcus Whitman 1 On Oct. 1, the Whitman girl's soccer team hosted the Big Green from Naples in a Finger Lakes West contest. Ellie Nemitz scored for Marcus Whitman, assisted by Michaela Commisso, but once again 1 goal would not be enough for the Wildcats. Naples countered with 2 goals of their own and held on for the 2-1 win. Katrina Meyer had 9 saves in goal for Whitman. Marcus Whitman is 1-5 in Finger Lakes West action. High School Golf Page 2 of 2 - Mustangs 235 Pal-Mac 239 The Penn Yan Mustang boy's golf team moved into a third place tie in the Finger Lakes East standings with a close fought, 235-239 win over visiting Pal-Mac at Lakeside Country Club in Penn Yan Sept. 28. Bryce Johnson shot a 45 to lead the Orange and Blue golfers. Andrew Christensen and John Travis carded 46's for Penn Yan. The Mustang's season record now stands at 6-4 in the league and 6-5 overall. Girl's Volleyball Penn Yan 3 Waterloo 1 The Penn Yan Mustang girl's volleyball team defeated Waterloo 3-1 in a Finger Lakes East match played in Waterloo Sept. 29. With the win, Penn Yan improves their FL East mark to 4-2. They are tied with Geneva and Newark for first place in the league. The Mustang's win against Waterloo was sparked by a 6 dig, 6 kill, 4 aces performance by Emily Wunder. Sydney Bloom added 11 digs and 7 kills, while Jessica Covell chipped in 14 digs and 5 aces. The Penn Yan netsters are now 8-2 overall. High School Cross Country Penn Yan And Marcus Whitman Teams Compete At Whitman The Penn Yan Mustang Cross Country teams traveled to Marcus Whitman High School Sept. 29 to compete in a meet against host Whitman, Waterloo, and Lyons. In the boy's competition, host Whitman defeated Waterloo 25-30, Lyons 19-41, and Penn Yan 16-43 to win the event. The Penn Yan harriers also lost to Waterloo 15-45 and Lyons 26-31. For the Wildcat runners, Gabe Stash finished 1st, Nate Mayton 2nd, Stephen Borsiuk 5th, and Tyler Schwarz 9th. Penn Yan's best finisher was Nick Kinsey in 12th place. Whitman improved their team record to 10-1, best in the W-FL Central. Penn Yan falls to 2-7 in the W/FL East. In the girl's meet on Tuesday, Waterloo defeated Penn Yan 18-43. The Lyons and Marcus Whitman teams ran incomplete. For the Mustangs, Macy Nicholson finished in 3rd place while teammate Katie Voak came in 7th place. Amanda Cline was Whitman's best runner, coming in 11th place. The Penn Yan team improved their season mark to 5-4 in the W/FL East. Marcus Whitman is 0-9 in the W/FL Central. By Gary Pinneo
